\title{synthsdtm: Parametrized Synthetic SDTM Simulator}
\description{
A study-agnostic engine that generates synthetic, CDISC SDTMIG 3.4 -shaped clinical trial datasets from a single machine-readable study configuration. The study (cohorts, design, visit grid, test panels, rate knobs) lives entirely in the config; the standard (variable order, labels, types, Controlled Terminology) lives in a resolved spec. Generation is deterministic and seeded, so the same inputs and seed produce identical output, and shape-domain row counts are a closed-form function of the structural inputs. A three-tier accuracy checker (Shape, Conformance, Cross-domain) recomputes the expected shape from the config and asserts on it, and an optional exporter writes SAS Transport (XPT v5) for CDISC CORE.
